{
  "texts": [
    "Twenty-six participants took part in the experiment and completed 60 trials per condition.",
    "The data were rereferenced to average reference, high-pass filtered at 0.25 Hz 123 Fig. 1 The stimuli.",
    "In the experimental condition, the participants saw a normal face (top), and in the control conditions either a blurred (left) or scrambled (right) face and low-pass filtered at 30 Hz.",
    "Subsequently, the data was corrected for artifacts using an independent component analysis and segmented in time-windows from -500 ms to 1500 ms relative to stimulus onset.",
    "A baseline correction from -300 ms to 0 ms was applied."
  ]
}